{
  "texts": [
    "The modelling datasets utilized in the present study are freely available at https:// kipp. idrug lab.",
    "Molecular representations calculationIn this study, five molecular fingerprints including Morgan fingerprints (ECFP-like, 1024-bits) [56], MACCS keys (166-bits) [57], AtomParis fingerprints (1024bits) [58], FP2 fingerprints (1024-bits) [59] and 2D pharmacophore fingerprints (PharmacoPFP, 38-bits) [60] were used to construct fingerprint-based predictive models.",
    "A set of 208 RDKit molecular descriptors (termed RDKitDes) was chosen for the development of descriptor-based predictive models.",
    "The fingerprints and descriptors were calculated using open source RDKit software (http:// www. rdkit.",
    "org/, version: 2020.03.1).In a molecular graph, the atomic and atomic pair features are used together as a feature matrix [61]."
  ]
}